SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1036
By Hensley
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the 2026 Mule Day
Court First Runner-Up, Phynlee Ryan Keeling.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
young citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as
outstanding Tennesseans of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Phynlee Ryan Keeling, who was recently
selected as the 2026 Mule Day Court First Runner-Up; and
WHEREAS, the daughter of Blair and Lacey Keeling, Phynlee Keeling is currently a
junior at Culleoka Unit School, where she is on the honor roll and in the top-five of her class;
she is actively involved in leadership and service through Youth Leadership Maury, the
Columbia Mayor's Youth Council, and the Maury County Junior Fair Board; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Keeling is also a dedicated student athlete and has played every girls'
sport offered at Culleoka Unit School, earning All-District and All-Tournament honors in both
softball and basketball; and
WHEREAS, Phynlee Keeling's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride
for her family, her community, and the citizens of Maury County; and
WHEREAS, the Mule Day Queen and her court play a prominent role in the promotion of
Mule Day, participating in media interviews and serving as hostesses during the festivities; and
WHEREAS, 2026 Mule Day Court First Runner-Up Phynlee Keeling epitomizes the spirit
of distinction and the commitment to greatness that are characteristic of true Tennesseans; her
dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect and admiration of this body; and
SJR1036
016786
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly find it appropriate to pause in their
deliberations to acknowledge and applaud this young woman for her remarkable achievement;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Phynlee Ryan Keeling
upon being selected as the 2026 Mule Day Court First Runner-Up, extending to her our best
wishes for every future success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
